HOUSE BILL 1617
J1, L2 6lr1146
By: Delegates Alston, Coley, Harrison, Ivey, Roberson, Roberts, Taylor, and Toles
Introduced and read first time: February 19, 2026
Assigned to: Rules and Executive Nominations
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public Health – Health Innovation Zones – Establishment
3 FOR the purpose of authorizing the local zoning authority in a county to designate a health
4 innovation zone if an area meets certain criteria; requiring a county, if the local
5 zoning authority designates a health innovation zone, to establish, by law, certain
6 incentives; requiring the Prince George’s County Council to designate a health
7 innovation zone in certain areas; authorizing the Prince George’s County Council to
8 designate additional health innovation zones in certain areas; requiring the
9 Governor to include an appropriation in the annual budget bill for the Maryland
10 Economic Development Corporation to encourage certain entities to locate in a
11 health innovation zone in Prince George’s County; exempting certain entities from
12 local zoning and land use laws; and generally relating to health innovation zones.
13 BY adding to
14 Article – Health – General
15 Section 20–14A–01 through 20–14A–04 to be under the new subtitle “Subtitle 14A.
16 Health Innovation Zones”
17 Annotated Code of Maryland
18 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
19 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
20 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
21 Article – Health – General
22 SUBTITLE 14A. HEALTH INNOVATION ZONES.
23 20–14A–01.
24 IN THIS SUBTITLE, “HEALTH INNOVATION ZONE” MEANS A CONTIGUOUS
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *hb1617*

2 HOUSE BILL 1617
1 GEOGRAPHIC AREA THAT:
2 (1) DEMONSTRATES MEASURABLE AND DOCUMENTED HEALTH
3 DISPARITIES AND POOR HEALTH OUTCOMES, INCLUDING HIGH RATES OF:
4 (I) MATERNAL HEALTH COMPLICATIONS;
5 (II) NEWBORN HEALTH COMPLICATIONS; AND
6 (III) CHRONIC AND INFECTIOUS DISEASES;
7 (2) IS POPULATED BY:
8 (I) COMMUNITIES OF COLOR;
9 (II) COMMUNITIES WITH LOW–INCOME HOUSEHOLDS;
10 (III) COMMUNITIES WITH A HIGH IMMIGRANT POPULATION; OR
11 (IV) ECONOMICALLY DISADVANTAGED COMMUNITIES; AND
12 (3) IS SMALL ENOUGH TO ALLOW FOR THE INCENTIVES UNDER THIS
13 SUBTITLE TO HAVE A SIGNIFICANT IMPACT ON IMPROVING HEALTH OUTCOMES AND
14 REDUCING HEALTH DISPARITIES, INCLUDING RACIAL, ETHNIC, GEOGRAPHIC, AND
15 DISABILITY–RELATED HEALTH DISPARITIES IN RURAL COMMUNITIES.
16 20–14A–02.
17 (A) SUBJECT TO § 20–14A–03 OF THIS SUBTITLE, THE LOCAL ZONING
18 AUTHORITY OF A COUNTY MAY DESIGNATE A HEALTH INNOVATION ZONE IF THE
19 AREA TO BE DESIGNATED:
20 (1) IS A FOOD OR HEALTH CARE DESERT;
21 (2) HAS A HIGH CONCENTRATION OF:
22 (I) CANCER;
23 (II) DIABETES;
24 (III) HEART DISEASE; OR
25 (IV) HYPERTENSION; AND

HOUSE BILL 1617 3
1 (3) HAS A LOW PREVALENCE OF GROCERY STORES, PHARMACIES,
2 PRIMARY CARE PROVIDERS, AND SPECIALTY CARE PROVIDERS.
3 (B) IF A LOCAL ZONING AUTHORITY OF A COUNTY DESIGNATES A HEALTH
4 INNOVATION ZONE UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION, THE COUNTY SHALL
5 ESTABLISH, BY LAW, INCENTIVES THAT WILL BE PROVIDED TO GROCERY STORES,
6 PHARMACIES, PRIMARY CARE PROVIDERS, AND SPECIALTY CARE PROVIDERS THAT
7 LOCATE IN THE HEALTH INNOVATION ZONE.
8 20–14A–03.
9 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
10 INDICATED.
11 (2) “MEDCO” MEANS THE MARYLAND ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT
12 CORPORATION.
13 (3) “PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY BLUE LINE CORRIDOR” HAS THE
14 MEANING STATED IN § 10–601 OF THE ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT ARTICLE.
15 (B) THIS SECTION APPLIES ONLY TO PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY.
16 (C) THE PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY COUNCIL SHALL DESIGNATE A
17 HEALTH INNOVATION ZONE IN THE FOLLOWING AREAS:
18 (1) PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY BLUE LINE CORRIDOR; AND
19 (2) THE AREA LOCATED WITHIN 2 MILES OF THE BORDER BETWEEN
20 PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY AND THE DISTRICT OF COLUMBIA.
21 (D) THE PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY COUNCIL MAY DESIGNATE
22 ADDITIONAL HEALTH INNOVATION ZONES IF THE AREA TO BE DESIGNATED:
23 (1) IS A FOOD OR HEALTH CARE DESERT;
24 (2) HAS A HIGH CONCENTRATION OF:
25 (I) CANCER;
26 (II) DIABETES;
27 (III) HEART DISEASE; OR

4 HOUSE BILL 1617
1 (IV) HYPERTENSION; AND
2 (3) HAS A LOW PREVALENCE OF GROCERY STORES, PHARMACIES,
3 PRIMARY CARE PROVIDERS, AND SPECIALTY CARE PROVIDERS.
4 (E) BEGINNING IN FISCAL YEAR 2028, THE GOVERNOR SHALL INCLUDE IN
5 THE ANNUAL BUDGET BILL AN APPROPRIATION OF AT LEAST $5,000,000 TO
6 MEDCO TO ENCOURAGE GROCERY STORES, PHARMACIES, PRIMARY CARE
7 PROVIDERS, AND SPECIALTY CARE PROVIDERS TO LOCATE IN A HEALTH
8 INNOVATION ZONE ESTABLISHED UNDER THIS SECTION.
9 (F) BEGINNING JULY 1, 2028, MEDCO SHALL PROVIDE FUNDING TO
10 ENCOURAGE GROCERY STORES, PHARMACIES, PRIMARY CARE PROVIDERS, AND
11 SPECIALTY CARE PROVIDERS TO ESTABLISH A BUSINESS IN A HEALTH INNOVATION
12 ZONE ESTABLISHED UNDER THIS SECTION.
13 (G) MEDCO SHALL LOOK FOR ADDITIONAL FUNDING SOURCES TO
14 ENCOURAGE HEALTH INNOVATION BUSINESS GROWTH IN A HEALTH INNOVATION
15 ZONE ESTABLISHED UNDER THIS SECTION.
16 20–14A–04.
17 A GROCERY STORE, PHARMACY, PRIMARY CARE PROVIDER, AND SPECIALTY
18 CARE PROVIDER LOCATED IN A HEALTH INNOVATION ZONE ESTABLISHED UNDER
19 THIS SUBTITLE ARE NOT SUBJECT TO LOCAL ZONING OR LAND USE LAWS.
20 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
21 October 1, 2026.

